1:15:53.091 --> 1:15:55.969
<i>encrypting the data
and rendering
the systems unusable</i>

1:15:56.053 --> 1:15:57.763
<i>unless a ransom was paid.</i>

1:15:58.222 --> 1:16:00.641
<i>This more militant variant
of the hacker collective</i>

1:16:00.724 --> 1:16:03.227
<i>forced Scott Knowles,
the CTO of E Corp,</i>

1:16:03.310 --> 1:16:06.813
<i>to burn $5.9 million
in public view.</i>

1:16:07.481 --> 1:16:10.150
<i>Shortly thereafter pictures
surfaced on social media</i>

1:16:10.234 --> 1:16:12.653
<i>under the name
#OPdailyallowance.</i>

1:16:13.237 --> 1:16:16.073
<i>Now, this is considered
a direct response
to E Corp's unpopular program,</i>

1:16:16.406 --> 1:16:18.742
<i>which would lower
their daily cash</i>

1:16:18.825 --> 1:16:21.161
<i>withdrawal allowances
for customers to $50.</i>

1:16:22.579 --> 1:16:23.914
Some stunt, huh?

1:16:24.998 --> 1:16:27.918
Everybody's laughing
it off as a dumb prank,

1:16:28.001 --> 1:16:29.836
but these guys know
what they're doing.

1:16:31.255 --> 1:16:34.258
Never thought
that hard cash would
be this valuable right now.

1:16:35.759 --> 1:16:39.096
We're reliving Black Tuesday,
the Great Depression.

1:16:40.264 --> 1:16:42.099
Warning lights were flashing.

1:16:42.182 --> 1:16:44.768
I mean, in the last two years

1:16:45.018 --> 1:16:46.520
the Army Corps
of Engineers,

1:16:46.603 --> 1:16:48.689
the Energy Department,
the State Department,

1:16:48.814 --> 1:16:51.358
and the Office
of Personnel Management

1:16:51.441 --> 1:16:52.693
were all hacked.

1:16:53.610 --> 1:16:55.946
The government claimed
they were boosting security,

1:16:56.029 --> 1:16:57.656
but what came of it?

1:16:59.199 --> 1:17:00.867
The same as 1929.

1:17:03.287 --> 1:17:04.454
Shit hit the fan.

1:17:08.625 --> 1:17:12.296
An act like this
changes people,
changes society.

1:17:13.046 --> 1:17:14.548
I'm just having a drink.

1:17:15.549 --> 1:17:17.801
I'm sorry,

1:17:18.302 --> 1:17:21.013
and I'm rambling
like a fanatic.

1:17:23.807 --> 1:17:25.559
Is there something else
you want to talk about?

1:17:28.562 --> 1:17:30.147
The beaches of Barbados,

1:17:31.815 --> 1:17:33.900
espresso
on Rue Montmartre,

1:17:35.319 --> 1:17:37.237
sitting around a campfire
in the Adirondacks?

1:17:37.321 --> 1:17:38.488
I'm married.

1:17:40.657 --> 1:17:41.825
I'm Brock...

1:17:44.244 --> 1:17:46.246
And I know
you're Gideon Goddard.

1:17:50.083 --> 1:17:51.585
I watch way too much news.

1:17:51.668 --> 1:17:52.669
God.

1:17:54.004 --> 1:17:55.839
I can't believe I'm
a tabloid sensation.

1:17:56.923 --> 1:17:58.425
